definition: Ming Dynasty (1368-1644)/surname Ming/Ming (c. 2000 BC), fourth of the legendary Flame Emperors, 炎帝[Yan2 di4] descended from Shennong 神農|神农[Shen2 nong2] Farmer God

sentences.english: The hydrometric pendulum is sometimes used to determine flow velocities in open channels.
sentences.chinese: 測流速的擺錘有時用於確定明渠中的流速。

sentences.english: The open-channel flowing refers to a kind of flowage which has the free surface.
sentences.chinese: 明渠流動指的是具有自由流動表面的水流形式。

sentences.english: In 2002, hundreds of ships still passed through the dam's diversion channel on a daily basis.
sentences.chinese: 2002年，每天仍有數百艘船行經大壩的導流明渠。

sentences.english: In order to build the diversion channel, the workers blasted through solid rock.
sentences.chinese: 爲了建造導流明渠，工人炸開堅硬的岩石。

sentences.english: The study was to solve the trapezoidal open canal critical depth of water based on the pattern search algorithm.
sentences.chinese: 基於模式搜索算法求解梯形明渠的臨界水深。

sentences.english: The kinetic model agrees well with experimental data of polystyrene particles and that of natural sands in two-dimensional open-channel flows.
sentences.chinese: 模型與二維明渠流輕質沙和天然沙試驗資料符合很好。

sentences.english: Open Channel and Longitudinal Cofferdam Project Attributed to CGGC.
sentences.chinese: 承建的導流明渠和縱向圍堰工程。

sentences.english: The flow in open channel bends is one of the most familiar forms in hydropower projects.
